    "First, the cosine similarity is converted to the radius (Euclidian distance by 2(1 -cos)), to get 0.2. foot_0 Then, the radius of the hypersphere with 1000 documents inside (x) can be derived from the following equation:",
    "From the estimated x, the radius of a 1000 document search can be obtained to be 0.201076, which is only 0.53% larger than that of 200 documents (0.2).",
    "However, the 200 neighbor results lead to 2.8 billion (20*14 million) observations with a tsv file size of about 70 GB.",
    "In the case of 1000 neighbor extractions, the output size becomes five times as above, so that the cost performance to increase the size of neighbors is very poor.",
    "Therefore, we stick to the size of 200 neighbors for subsequent analysis."
